  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 200°C (400°F).",
    "Season the Mahi-mahi fillets with salt and black pepper.",
    "Heat 2 tbsp of olive oil in a large oven-safe skillet over medium-high heat.",
    "Brown the Mahi-mahi on both sides for 2-3 minutes, then set aside.",
    "Add the remaining 4 tbsp of olive oil, then the chopped onion and ginger.",
    "Saute until the onion is translucent, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the minced garlic and cook for another minute.",
    "Add the mustard powder and cook for 1 minute.",
    "Deglaze with the white wine, scraping the bottom of the skillet.",
    "Bring the liquid to a boil, then add the water and honey.",
    "Stir to combine and bring to a boil, then reduce the heat to a simmer.",
    "Return the Mahi-mahi to the skillet and spoon some of the broth over it.",
    "Transfer the skillet to the preheated oven and bake for 12-15 minutes, or until the fish is cooked through.",
    "Stir in the chopped capers, parsley, lemongrass, preserved lemon, cumin seeds, and coriander.",
    "Season with salt and black pepper to taste.",
    "Serve the fish with the sauce spooned over the top and garnished with crunchy sesame seeds, flaked almonds, and chopped parsley.",
    "Garnish with a lemon wedge, if desired.",
    "Bread the Mahi-mahi with breadcrumbs soaked in coconut oil.",
    "Garnish with bread crumbs and serve immediately.",
    "Garnish with bread crumbs, sesame seeds, flaked almonds and serve immediately."
  ],
